---
import fs from "node:fs";
import path from "node:path";
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

const canaryPath = path.resolve(process.cwd(), "public/canary.txt");
const canaryText = fs.existsSync(canaryPath)
  ? fs.readFileSync(canaryPath, "utf-8")
  : "";

const expiresMatch = /^Expires\s*:\s*(.+)$/m.exec(canaryText);
const fingerprintMatch = /^Fingerprint\s*:\s*(.+)$/m.exec(canaryText);
const issuedMatch = /^Issued\s*:\s*(.+)$/m.exec(canaryText);

const expires = expiresMatch ? expiresMatch[1].trim() : "PENDING";
const issued = issuedMatch ? issuedMatch[1].trim() : "PENDING";
const fingerprint = fingerprintMatch
  ? fingerprintMatch[1].trim()
  : "PENDING FIRST RENEWAL";
---

<Base title="Warrant canary --- ai-for-less-suffering.com">
  <h1 class="mb-2 text-2xl text-zinc-100">Warrant canary</h1>
  <p class="mb-6 text-sm text-zinc-400">
    A public, PGP-signed statement that I have not received certain kinds of
    <a
      href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Foreign_Intelligence_Surveillance_Act"
      class="text-zinc-200 underline hover:text-zinc-100"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
      target="_blank">secret legal orders</a
    >. If I stop renewing it, assume I have. The absence of a renewal is the
    signal.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-6 text-sm text-zinc-400">
    The expiration time is intentionally set to 3 months. My thesis is that
    certain AI development efforts and AI policy measures need to act quickly
    --- but that the world ALSO must think long term. "We" (America, the world,
    humanity) owe it to the human race to use this technology correctly. This
    canary is a protest against FISA --- now --- Is the world thinking about how
    to use AI to reduce suffering? Or are they spying? Time to figure it out {
      `<3<3<3`
    } FUCK PALANTIR FUCK ISRAEL
  </p>

  <div
    id="canary-expired-banner"
    class="mb-6 hidden rounded border border-red-700 bg-red-950 p-4 text-sm text-red-200"
  >
    <strong class="text-red-100">EXPIRED.</strong> This canary was not renewed before
    its expiration date, or has not yet been signed. Treat the statement below as
    no longer attested. Assume compromise.
  </div>

  <section
    class="mb-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-2 text-xs text-zinc-400 sm:grid-cols-3"
  >
    <div>
      <div class="text-zinc-500">Issued</div>
      <div class="font-mono text-zinc-200">{issued}</div>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="text-zinc-500">Expires</div>
      <div class="font-mono text-zinc-200">{expires}</div>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="text-zinc-500">Fingerprint</div>
      <div class="font-mono break-all text-zinc-200">{fingerprint}</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-6">
    <h2 class="mb-2 text-sm text-zinc-500">Statement</h2>
    <pre
      class="overflow-x-auto rounded border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900 p-4 text-xs text-zinc-200">{canaryText || "canary.txt not found"}</pre>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-6">
    <h2 class="mb-2 text-sm text-zinc-500">Downloads</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm">
      <li>
        <a href="/canary.txt" class="text-zinc-100 hover:underline"
          >canary.txt</a
        >
        <span class="text-zinc-500"> --- the signed plaintext statement</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="/canary.txt.asc" class="text-zinc-100 hover:underline"
          >canary.txt.asc</a
        >
        <span class="text-zinc-500"> --- detached PGP signature</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="/canary-key.asc" class="text-zinc-100 hover:underline"
          >canary-key.asc</a
        >
        <span class="text-zinc-500">
          --- public key (import once, verify forever)</span
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-6">
    <h2 class="mb-2 text-sm text-zinc-500">Verify</h2>
    <pre
      class="overflow-x-auto rounded border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900 p-4 text-xs text-zinc-200">curl -O https://ai-for-less-suffering.com/canary-key.asc
curl -O https://ai-for-less-suffering.com/canary.txt
curl -O https://ai-for-less-suffering.com/canary.txt.asc
gpg --import canary-key.asc
gpg --verify canary.txt.asc canary.txt</pre>
    <p class="mt-3 text-xs text-zinc-500">
      Look for <code class="text-zinc-300">Good signature</code> and a key fingerprint
      that matches the one above. If the fingerprint is different, or verification
      fails, do not trust the statement.
    </p>
  </section>

  <script is:inline define:vars={{ expires }}>
    (() => {
      const banner = document.getElementById("canary-expired-banner");
      if (!banner) return;
      const parsed = Date.parse(expires + "T23:59:59Z");
      if (Number.isNaN(parsed) || parsed < Date.now()) {
        banner.classList.remove("hidden");
      }
    })();
  </script>
</Base>
